fields.description:
When the user removes a page, Confluence searches for all incoming links.  To do so, it runs this query:
{code:java}
select page1_.CONTENTID as col_0_0_, outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY as col_1_0_, outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE as col_2_0_,cast(count(outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE) as int4) as col_3_0_from LINKS outgoingli0_ cross join CONTENT page1_ cross join SPACES space2_ cross join CONTENT contentent3_where page1_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and page1_.SPACEID=space2_.SPACEID and outgoingli0_.CONTENTID=contentent3_.CONTENTID and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY=space2_.LOWERSPACEKEY and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE=page1_.LOWERTITLE and contentent3_.CONTENT_STATUS='current' and(outgoingli0_.CONTENTID not in (select page4_.CONTENTIDfrom CONTENT page4_ left outer join CONFANCESTORS ancestors5_ on page4_.CONTENTID=ancestors5_.DESCENDENTID left outer join CONTENT contentent6_ on ancestors5_.ANCESTORID=contentent6_.CONTENTIDwhere page4_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and (page4_.PREVVER is null) and page4_.CONTENT_STATUS='current' and(contentent6_.CONTENTID='1487209916' or page4_.CONTENTID='1487209916' ))) and(outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE in (select page7_.LOWERTITLEfrom CONTENT page7_where page7_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and (page7_.PARENTID='1487209916' or page7_.CONTENTID='1487209916') and (page7_.PREVVER is null) andpage7_.CONTENT_STATUS='current')) and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY='emps'group by page1_.CONTENTID , outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY , outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE {code}
The above query can be very slow in large environments, up to around 30 seconds.  The query could be optimized as such:
{code:java}
select page1_.CONTENTID as col_0_0_, outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY as col_1_0_, outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE as col_2_0_,cast(count(outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE) as int4) as col_3_0_from LINKS outgoingli0_ cross join CONTENT page1_ cross join SPACES space2_ cross join CONTENT contentent3_where page1_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and page1_.SPACEID=space2_.SPACEID and outgoingli0_.CONTENTID=contentent3_.CONTENTID and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY=space2_.LOWERSPACEKEY and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE=page1_.LOWERTITLE and contentent3_.CONTENT_STATUS='current' and(outgoingli0_.CONTENTID not in (select page4_.CONTENTIDfrom CONTENT page4_ left outer join CONFANCESTORS ancestors5_ on page4_.CONTENTID=ancestors5_.DESCENDENTID left outer join CONTENT contentent6_ on ancestors5_.ANCESTORID=contentent6_.CONTENTIDwhere ( page4_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and (page4_.PREVVER is null) and page4_.CONTENT_STATUS='current' andpage4_.CONTENTID='1487209916' ) unionselect page4_.CONTENTIDfrom CONTENT page4_ left outer join CONFANCESTORS ancestors5_ on page4_.CONTENTID=ancestors5_.DESCENDENTID left outer join CONTENT contentent6_ on ancestors5_.ANCESTORID=contentent6_.CONTENTIDwhere ( page4_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and (page4_.PREVVER is null) and page4_.CONTENT_STATUS='current' andcontentent6_.CONTENTID='1487209916' ) )) and(outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE in (select page7_.LOWERTITLEfrom CONTENT page7_where page7_.CONTENTTYPE='PAGE' and (page7_.PARENTID='1487209916' or page7_.CONTENTID='1487209916') and (page7_.PREVVER is null) andpage7_.CONTENT_STATUS='current')) and outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY='emps'group by page1_.CONTENTID , outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTSPACEKEY , outgoingli0_.LOWERDESTPAGETITLE {code}
This query returns the same data, but does so instantly.

h2. Steps to reproduce

# Create a user in JIRA with an apostrophe (') in the username - e.g. *Lucas.o'reilly*;
# Create JIRA directory in Confluence and Sync;
#* (i) Although Confluence UI doesn't allow the creation of usernames with special characters, syncing with JIRA will successfully insert the troublesome username in the database;
# Create a space and allow Anonymous access to it (view and edit);
# Make editions without being logged in (anonymous update);
# Check the test user's profile;


h3. Expected results

No activity logged since we haven't even logged in with this user.


h3. Actual results

Every update made while accessing Confluence anonymously is displayed under our test user's Activity.


h3. Workaround

Edit the affected username(s) and remove the apostrophe (').

h3. Additional details

This happens for every user with an apostrophe in the username. All of them will show the same activity related to anonymous updates.

Looking at the Profile Activity's source code, we can see that Confluence probably fails to find the affected usernames and then assumes they are anonymous.

h5. Environment:
Confluence 6.7.0, PostgreSQL 9.5, Google Chrome
h5. Bug description
Livesearch macro certain characters in search previews
{code:title=Characters}
"
'
&
<
>
{code}
{code:title=Livesearch preview results for each, respectively}
&quot;
&#39;
&amp;
&lt;
&gt;
{code}

in search results preview
h5. Steps to replicate
* Create new page with & character in page title for example "test & test"
 !Screenshot_20180327_093436.png|thumbnail! 
* Go to different page, add livesearch macro, save the page. 
* Search for page with & character in pagename

h5. Expected results
 Search results correctly encode & character in results preview  

h5. Actual results
& is encoded as 
{noformat}
&amp; 
{noformat}
 !Screenshot_20180327_093414.png|thumbnail! 
h5. Notes:
Issue is not visible when using main searchbox
